<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1919-08-11T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1919-08-11T00:00:00-05:00" n="727" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d727">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">861.24/181 a</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Third Assistant Secretary of State</hi>
                                (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Long</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Elanco Forwarding Corporation
                                    of New York</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1919-08-11"><hi rend="italic">August 11,
                                1919</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Gentlemen</hi>: The ship <hi rend="italic">Redondo</hi> which carries a cargo of flour and which was consigned
                            to Falmouth for orders, should now proceed to Reval and report to the
                            representative of the American Relief Administration who will issue the
                            necessary instructions for the discharge of this cargo.</p>
                        <p rend="center">. . . . . . .</p>
                        <p>I am [etc.]</p>
                        <closer><signed><persName><hi rend="smallcaps">Breckinridge
                                    Long</hi></persName></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>